tweet: I had assumed that I’d have to sneak in a reference to queer stuff in the season finale or something, or some blink and you’ll miss it joke. But once I knew they wanted to tell the story truthfully to my vision I was like GREAT, I want this! And that! And three of those!

name: hamish steele 🏳️‍🌈
description: Creator of DEAD END coming soon to Netflix | writes comics, loves gators | cohost of @wakingknpodcast | streams on saturdays | he/they | #actuallyautistic
tweet: It took a while to shake that off, and working of a kids cartoon with a trans lead, numerous queer characters, actors, crew, storylines etc made me think that maybe maybeee this censorship was finally coming to an end. But I’m starting to think I’ll never be so lucky again.

name: hamish steele 🏳️‍🌈
description: Creator of DEAD END coming soon to Netflix | writes comics, loves gators | cohost of @wakingknpodcast | streams on saturdays | he/they | #actuallyautistic
tweet: - every time they would mention the queer characters and storylines from the book, I would change subjects. They asked if I was uncomfortable. It was actually a survival tactic I’d developed over years of pitching queer stuff and getting shot down, gaslit, ignored, etc.

name: hamish steele 🏳️‍🌈
description: Creator of DEAD END coming soon to Netflix | writes comics, loves gators | cohost of @wakingknpodcast | streams on saturdays | he/they | #actuallyautistic
